<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="nesting">Nesting</h3>
<p>Although possible, Boxes of the same <code>ord</code> should not be nested inside each other. Nesting a secondary Box inside a primary Box is ok:</p>
<code-sample>
  <mw-card>
    <h3 class="mar-t-0">Terms of service</h3>
    <p>Boxes of the same <code>ord</code> should not be nested inside each other. Nesting a secondary Box inside a primary Box is ok. You must agree to these guidelines to continue.</p>
    <mw-card ord="secondary"><label for="agree"><input id="agree" type="checkbox"> I agree.</label></mw-card>
  </mw-card>
</code-sample>
<h3 id="header-footer">Box header</h3>
<p>Because a Box header is more tricky than it seems (compensating for default padding), it doesn't get any special styles. However, it just takes a few classes to get a nice Box header:</p>
<code-sample>
  <mw-card class="pad-0">
    <header class="pad-md bg-gray-1 brd-b">Header</header>
    <div class="pad-md">
      Content
    </div>
  </mw-card>
</code-sample>
<h3 id="a11y">Accessibility</h3>
